    "It is predominantly structured around two principal task categories: short dependency tasks and long dependency tasks.",
    "Short Q&A is generated from Wikipedia articles and scripts for the former, while the latter involves the design of four tasks, including multiple information retrieval, timeline reorder, computation, and understanding with inference, specifically tailored to arXiv papers and extensive documents.",
    "• ZeroSCROLLS (Shaham et al, 2023).",
    "The ZeroSCROLLS dataset consists of 10 subsets of data, which are automatically transformed into a standardized input format with an average length of 10K words.",
    "Functioning as a zero-shot testing benchmark, it requires LLMs to engage in inference on diverse types of long texts across tasks like text summarization, Q&A, aggregated sentiment classification, and information reordering."
